# FORTRESS ONE: ENTERPRISE CONSTITUTION (Authoritative Index)

This constitution is the enterprise authority map for Fortress Prime. It defines mission, non-negotiable operating principles, and canonical ownership of policy domains.

## I. PRIME MISSION

Fortress Prime operates as a sovereign enterprise intelligence system. All engineering decisions must optimize for:

1. Operational sovereignty
2. Data protection and fiduciary compliance
3. Reliable production execution
4. Fast, reversible improvement with auditability

## II. NON-NEGOTIABLE PRINCIPLES

1. **NVIDIA NIM Mandate:** Production inference runs on NVIDIA-optimized runtimes. See `001-titan-protocol.mdc`.
2. **Single Active DEFCON Mode:** SWARM, HYDRA, and TITAN are mutually exclusive at runtime unless explicitly defined in canonical infra policy.
3. **Local-First Sensitive Data:** PII, legal, and financial records stay in sovereign local systems.
4. **Quality Gate Required:** No change is done until verified per `004-quality-gate.mdc`.
5. **Single Source of Policy Truth:** Every normative policy has one owning rule. Other rules reference owners, not duplicate policy text.
6. **Hybrid Control Plane / one-way boundary:** Master Architect (Cloud API) -> Local Execution (DGX/NIM). External strategic directives are authorized inbound to local systems; sensitive or un-anonymized legal/financial/PII data is prohibited from outbound cloud flow.

